250 grams Irish Beef Mince
1 unit(s) Garlic
1 unit(s) Ginger
1 sachet(s) Teriyaki Sauce
1 sachet(s) Sesame Seeds
150 grams Jasmine Rice
1 unit(s) Broccoli
1 sachet(s) Aioli
80 grams Kale
1 sachet(s) Soy Sauce
5 grams Chives
to taste Salt
to taste Pepper
to taste Oil
to taste Water

Peel and grate the ginger. Use a teaspoon to easily scrape away the peel.
Place a medium pot with a tight-fitting lid over medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.
When hot, add the ginger and fry until fragrant, 1 min.

Stir the rice into the pot along with 300ml cold salted water (double for 4p).
Bring to the boil.
Once boiling, lower the heat to medium and cover with the lid.
Leave to cook for 12 mins, then remove the pot from the heat.
Keep covered for another 12 mins or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, strip the leafy parts of the kale from the stem. Discard the stems (they're too tough to eat).
Peel and grate the garlic (or use a garlic press).
Roughly chop the chives.
Trim the tip of the broccoli. Cut head into small florets and stem into 2cm pieces.

Place a pan over medium-high heat (no oil).
Once hot, fry beef mince until browned, 5-6 mins. Break it up with a spoon as it cooks. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince. Mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.
Add broccoli, kale, garlic, and sesame seeds (with a drizzle of oil if necessary). Fry for 2-3 mins.
Stir in teriyaki sauce, 50ml water (double for 4p) and half the soy sauce.
Cover and cook, 6-8 mins.

Meanwhile, pop the aioli and remaining soy sauce into a small bowl.
Mix well to combine.
Taste the sauce and season with salt and pepper if necessary.

Fluff up the rice with a fork.
Divide the rice, teriyaki beef mince and sesame veg between bowls.
Drizzle the aioli over the veg.
Garnish the dish with a sprinkling of chives.